Soldiers attached to 144 Battalion, Ukwa Army Headquarters, in Ukwa West Local Government Area of Abia State have arrested two suspected robbers and kidnappers operating in Aba and its environs. It was gathered that while two other suspected robbers and kidnappers escaped arrest, the soldiers, after conducting a search, found three pistols, cache of yet-to-be expended bullets, a phone, jewellery and cash. Sources at the battalion, who gave the ages of the suspects as 31 and 32, said the soldiers also recovered a Toyota Corolla Sports Utility Vehicle, which the hoodlums snatched from the owner on Ehere Road, Ogbor Hill, off Aba-Ikot Ekpene Expressway. 